Supporters do not just want a donation link. They want to understand what is changing, what is still uncertain, and why the case still matters.

## Updates make the work legible

Emergency care is rarely a straight line. Updates help people see the real shape of a case: the stabilizing, the waiting, the setbacks, and the wins.

## Transparency builds durability

When families and supporters both understand where a case stands, trust becomes more durable. That matters for one-time donors and for the long-term health of the lifeline.

## What a useful update includes

Useful updates explain what changed, what the care team is watching next, and what the remaining financial needs actually cover.